### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

platform-browser

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

**Context**

I have some sticky content I want to render outside of app-root - can provide additional details as to why, but it has to do with smooth scrolling and animations.

```
    const embeddedViewRef = viewContainerRef.createEmbeddedView(stickyContent);
    embeddedViewRef.detectChanges();


     const stickyContentContainer = this.document?.querySelector(
        ".content-parent.sticky-content"
      );
      this.renderer = rendererFactory.createRenderer(null, null);
      this.renderer.appendChild(this.stickyContentContainer, node);
```

**Issue**

Using renderer.appendChild causes hydration to fail (which is expected due to the use of querySelector I suppose).
However, the following I believe may be bugs:

- When adding ngSkipHydration: true to the host of the component calling this code, hydration fails. When commenting out the this.renderer.appendChild line, hydration runs succesfully. If I add ngSkipHydration: true, two parents up though, hydration runs succesfully.
- When adding the ngSkipHydration attribute to the div where the dynamically rendered content should be rendered, hydration still fails.

If you can confirm that there's interest in looking into this I'd be happy to create a repro.


