### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

router

### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

So this weird behavior only occurs when I open the website for the first time. After I refresh the website it works fine. 

The injection inside `CanActivateFn` function does not retrieve the latest signal value after the signal is updated.

This is the `CanActivateFn`:

```
export const RegisteredGuard: CanActivateFn = (route, state) => {
  return inject(AuthService).isUserInRoles(['registered']) ? true : inject(NavigationService).router.createUrlTree(['/login']);
};

export const AllContentGuard: CanActivateFn = (route, state) => {
  return !environment.protectAllContentWithAuthentication ? true :
    inject(AuthService).isUserInRoles(['registered']) ? true : inject(NavigationService).router.createUrlTree(['/login']);
};
```

This is the `AuthService`:

```
export class AuthService {
  auth: WritableSignal<IAuth | undefined>;

  constructor(
    private cookieService: CookieService,
    private nav: NavigationService,
    private notification: NotificationService
  ) {
    this.auth = this.initAuth();
  }

  private initAuth() {
    return signal(this.getCookieAuth());
  }

  private getCookieAuth() {
    const auth = this.cookieService.get('auth');
    return auth ? JSON.parse(auth) : undefined;
  }

  setAuth(auth: IAuth) {
    // Set cookie to expire in 30 days
    this.cookieService.set(
      'auth',
      JSON.stringify(auth),
      environment.authExpiresAfter
        ? new Date(Date.now() + environment.authExpiresAfter)
        : undefined
    );
    this.auth.set(auth);
  }

  removeAuth() {
    this.cookieService.delete('auth');
    this.auth.set(undefined);
  }

  logout() {
    this.removeAuth();
    this.notification.success('You have been logged out');
    this.nav.navigateByUrl('/login');
  }

  isUserInRoles(roles: string[]) {
    return this.auth()?.roles?.some((r) => roles.includes(r)) ?? false;
  }
}
```

This is my `app-route`:

```
export const routes: Routes = [
  ...accountRoute,
  {
    path: '',
    component: LayoutComponent,
    children: [
      {
        path: '',
        component: IndexPageComponent,
        pathMatch: 'full',
      },
      {
        path: 'index',
        component: IndexPageComponent,
      },
      {
        path: 'account',
        component: ProfilePageComponent,
      }
    ],
    canActivate: [AllContentGuard],
  },
];
```

The idea here is that all of my content is guarded by `AllContentGuard`. The user has to be logged in to be able to see the content. The problem here is that this code:

```
  isUserInRoles(roles: string[]) {
    return this.auth()?.roles?.some((r) => roles.includes(r)) ?? false;
  }
```

Does not get the `this.auth()` values correctly. It gives me `undefined`, even after I set the auth from this `login-page.component.ts`:

```
  async login() {
    this.loading.set(true);
    const res = await this.http.post<IAuth>('/login', null, {
      email: this.email(),
      password: this.password(),
    });
    this.loading.set(false);

    if (res) {
      if (res.error) {
        this.notification.error(res.msg);
      } else if (res.data) {
        this.auth.setAuth(res.data);

        // If user is not confirmed, redirect to confirm email page
        if (!res.data.confirmed) {
          this.notification.warning(this.str()('emailNotConfirmed'));
          setTimeout(() => this.nav.navigateByUrl('/confirm-email'), 1000);
        } else {
          this.notification.success(this.str()('loginSuccess'));
          this.nav.navigateToIndex();
        }
      }
    }
  }
```

I even tried to setup the navigation wrapped in `setTimeout()` to see if there is delay for the signal updates, but it is the same.

The problem only occurs when I go to `http://localhost:4201` as my app is hosted. If I refresh the page immediately after I open the website, it works fine, but not when first opening the web.

-----

The problem occurs only when I go to `http://localhost:4201`, which is redirected to `http://localhost:4201/login`. If I go by typing `http://localhost:4201/login`, it works fine.

So the flow is like this:

First open website -> go to `http://localhost:4201` -> got redirected for the first time from `CanActivateFn` by `AllContentGuard` to `http://localhost:4201/login` -> login and sets the auth -> Then the guard always retrieves undefined auth.

-----

**UPDATE**

Ok so, after getting redirected by the guard `AllContentGuard`, the guard loses the connection to the auth signal. It is no longer able to get the update from the signal.

Does redirecting using this:

```
inject(NavigationService).router.createUrlTree(['login'])
```
removes the connection with the signal? I am not sure

-----

